rComments: I wasn't very interested in this course before registering so I can't say I found the lectures to be interesting from the beginning so I might be a little biased on how boring the class was. Put that aside, he is a nice prof with great guidelines for the exams, so you can do great in the course with easy effort. Be prepared to be bored though!

This professor is very passionate about his teachings, has sound knowledge of economics of developing countries and extremely helpful. He welcomes discussions and is very clear on what the expectations are for the course. Truly a Great professor!

Very helpful, and a knowledgeable teacher. If you are unfamiliar with his accent then it can make hearing and understanding difficult. Sometimes reads of slides, but his slides are well done. Sometimes he's as clear as crystal and sometimes you will find yourself confused.

Very helpful and knowledgeable.  Although he teaches in his second language, he is receptive to any questions to help clarify answers.  Always available and hospitable during office hours.  Overall, friendly, knowledgeable, engaging.  You can do well in his course if you apply yourself.
Nice prof, always help when you ask for it. Pretty detailed slides that are helpful.
Helpful professor, has a lot of knowledge in the material.  Exams are consistent of what we see in class or textbook.

ugh.. you can definitely pass his course but lean nothing.  very dry class and strong accent.  just simply read slides at home and no need to attend class, seems like he doesnt have any teaching methodology  at all... recommend for people who dont have time for class but aim to pass.
You can see he has the knowledge but doesnt know how to pass it, all I can say is no need to attedn the class to pass but as a teacher, bad! Dont take his class.
